The paper deals with malware detection and analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method, MalPaCA, involves clustering temporal behavior observed in malware's network traces, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The use of network traces also falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an evaluation method for the obtained clusters, which involves software engineering principles (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of visualization techniques to aid in cluster evaluation, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
